2-05\nDone this week: Slipped the promised design review; rescheduling for later this week.\nPlan for next week: Realign with the partner team and reset the delivery date.\n\n[DELAYED] Q1 2026 [February]: Warm-cache eviction policy (february-2026)\nLeader Engineer: Quinn Yates\nProgress: 22% | Due: 28 Feb\nLink: https://example.invalid/objectives/MBETA-2602-06\nDone this week: Waiting on infra migration that was pushed to the next quarter.\nPlan for next week: Reassign to a different owner so the current one can help elsewhere.\n\nBLOCKERS / RISKS\n- [Blocker] Q1 2026 [February]: Warm-cache eviction policy: External vendor SLA slipping; no eta.\n  Leader Engineer: Quinn Yates | Owner: Quinn Yates | Days open: n/a\n- [Risk] Q1 2026 [February]: Zero-downtime restart choreography: Follow-on ticket landed late; scope grew mid-sprint.\n  Leader Engineer: Tomo Ilves | Owner: Tomo Ilves | Days open: n/a\n- [Risk] Q1 2026 [February]: Service topology drift alarm: Follow-on ticket landed late; scope grew mid-sprint.\n  Leader Engineer: Frida Ohno | Owner: Frida Ohno | Days open: n/a\n- [Risk] Q1 2026 [February]: Feature flag rollout guardrails: Downstream integration test suite is flaky; may hide a regression at go-live.\n  Leader Engineer: Sana Rowe | Owner: Sana Rowe | Days open: n/a\n- [Risk] Q1 2026 [February]: Observability sampling refresh: Downstream integration test suite is flaky; may hide a regression at go-live.\n  Leader Engineer: Jules Cabrera | Owner: Jules Cabrera | Days open: n/a\n\nKind Regards\nEngineering Manager"
